data.name: TextBox1.Text
data.value:
To add an item to a list you must first select an existing item on the list right next to where you wish to add. Then you must right-click on that item and determine if you wish to add the new listing above or below the selection.
Now depending on which list you are working with you'll be presented with a dialog asking you for the information needed for that particular list. Simply plug in the needed information and hit "OK".

data.name: TextBox2.Text
data.value:
Similar to adding a new listing, you must first select an existing item next to where you wish to add the new category. Then you must right-click the selected item and determine if you wish the new category to be above or below the selection; select your choice.
Now, when you are presented with the "Add" dialog, instead of entering an ID number (or Name as it is called for Locations) you would use the keywords "GCat", "Cat", or "Sub" to create Global-Categories, Categories, or Sub-Categories respectively.
Note: There is currently no error checking when added new categories, so you must ensure that you have a proper tree-structure. I.e. Do not add a Global-Category immediately followed by a Sub-Category.
